==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English, from Old English ''[[sæd|sǣd]]'', ''[[sed|sēd]]''. Related to [[sow]].

===Adjective===
'''seed''' {{notcomp}}

#Held in reserve for future growth.
#:''seed money''
#:''Don't eat your seed corn''

